{{Alt Class|no=7.77|ent=5|ext=3|env=5}}
<div class="header>General Description</div>
{{Blurimage|file=darkwater.png|hovertext=Faded Memories|caption=The depths of Level 7.77.}}
'''Level 7.77''', alternatively known as ''"Atlantis"'' or ''"After The Flood"'', is a sublevel of [[Level 7]] of the Backrooms.

Stretching across an indeterminably large distance, the level takes the form of a contemporary metropolitan area, left in a state of disrepair and submerged entirely in a sea of non-anomalous salt water and [[Almond Water]], which is presumably infinitely deep and extends endlessly upwards from the bottom of the ocean floor. Strangely, despite the infinite size and depth of the ocean above, the water pressure remains at survivable amounts. The reason for this is unknown, but [[The Kauer Research Organization|Kauer]] scientists have theorized that it is due to various gravitational anomalies affecting the level and, by extension, the ocean.

The level's only source of natural illumination comes from a substance known as ''Neon Water'' (not to be confused with its [[Temporary Manifestation|more ephemeral counterpart]]) within the sea of the locale. Although this substance has no significant positive or negative properties for wanderers, it perpetually emits a dim blue-green light when mixed with water, providing the rest of the level with a weak light source and serving as the substance's namesake.

Heavy waves are common in the level, with some large enough to completely knock out a person, as well as toppling and altering the level's underwater structures. Also, due to the complete lack of air within the area, many wanderers who enter the level end up drowning in the endless sea, having been unable to make it out of the level before meeting their demise. Consequently, the level is extremely dangerous to enter without an alternate source of air, such as a scuba diving suit.

'''Although difficult, there are some ways wanderers can survive in Level 7.77 without the proper equipment.'''

<div class="header>Interior Area</div>
<div class="onlydark">
===<span style= "font-family:Aleo; text-shadow: 1.5px 1.5px 0px #000000, 1px 1px 10px #45392d, 0px 0px 1px #000000; color:white;"><center>'''The Underwater City'''</center></span>===
</div>
<div class="onlylight">
===<span style= "font-family:Aleo; text-shadow: 1.5px 1.5px 0px #1b1b1b, 1px 1px 10px #45392d, 0px 0px 1px #FFFFFF; color:black;"><center>'''The Underwater City'''</center></span>===
</div>
<div style="text-align:center;">
[[File:Darkwater.png|center|500x300px]]
'''The Underwater City''' is the biggest region of Level 7.77 that lies fairly deep within the level, spanning nearly the entirety of the level. It is a large submerged urban area, taking the appearance of a ruined ancient city. '''The Underwater City''' mostly consists of streets and building structures. The Drowned can also seldom appear in the city. Navigation through the area is inconvenient, as many of these structures have poor structural integrity, with most of them already having or are on the verge of crumbling downwards, acting as blockades. The collapsed rubble and debris split the streets into many branches, further complicating the region’s layout.

Neon Water provides weak light within the city, but it is barely enough to see faint outlines of nearby structures, and not enough to determine distance or direction. As visibility is low, wanderers frequently get lost when attempting to explore the level, eventually dying due to the lack of air. Therefore, it is advised to stay near the surface and remember a section’s layout before diving deep into the city.
<div class="onlydark">
===<span style= "font-family:Aleo; text-shadow: 1.5px 1.5px 0px #000000, 1px 1px 10px #45392d, 0px 0px 1px #000000; color:white;"><center>'''The Skeleton Reefs'''</center></span>===
</div>
<div class="onlylight">
===<span style= "font-family:Aleo; text-shadow: 1.5px 1.5px 0px #1b1b1b, 1px 1px 10px #45392d, 0px 0px 1px #FFFFFF; color:black;"><center>'''The Skeleton Reefs'''</center></span>===
</div>[[File:Reef.jpg|center|500x300px]]
A low-quality image of tunnels in '''the Skeleton Reefs'''. Photographer unknown.

'''The Skeleton Reefs''' are an area mostly made out of debris, containing an abundance of reef-like structures made from skeletal remains and other materials with sharp angles and narrow tunnels. Navigation is next to impossible, as the large amounts of debris combined with the complex reef structures create a near-inescapable maze for wanderers, challenging them to sort through the wreckage.

'''The Skeleton Reefs''' also pose a significant danger to wanderers due to the level’s heavy waves. During these waves, nearby debris and reef structures start to shift. If one does not exit the area before this time, there is a high chance of them getting trapped within the reefs, unable to escape, and leading to eventual death. Therefore, it is advised to simply avoid the Skeleton Reefs unless otherwise.
<div class="onlydark">
===<span style= "font-family:Aleo; text-shadow: 1.5px 1.5px 0px #000000, 1px 1px 10px #45392d, 0px 0px 1px #000000; color:white;"><center>'''The Cemetery'''</center></span>===
</div>
<div class="onlylight">
===<span style= "font-family:Aleo; text-shadow: 1.5px 1.5px 0px #1b1b1b, 1px 1px 10px #45392d, 0px 0px 1px #FFFFFF; color:black;"><center>'''The Cemetery'''</center></span>===
</div>
[[File:Cemeteri.jpg|center]]
A photograph of a section of '''the Cemetery'''. Photographer whereabouts unknown.

'''The Cemetery''', as the name suggests, presents itself as a gigantic circular burial ground located in the middle of the Underwater City, with many markers and tombstones. Strangely, it is possible to breathe underwater when within the cemetery. Occasionally, one may come across a grave with a trident (with a similar appearance to the Greek God Poseidon’s weapon); it is unknown why this is the case. It is impossible to make contact with the tombstones, as mysterious forces seem to be protecting them.

If one digs through the sand in front of a gravestone, a wooden coffin will be unfolded (this is not the case for all of the gravestones). Opening the wooden coffin reveals nothing underneath; however, in rare instances, strange vines can be found growing within the coffin, seemingly from nothing. The Drowned can also be commonly found within this region. The area itself is relatively calm as it is unaffected by the waves and does not contain debris, with easy navigation. Therefore, it is advised to stay within this area if one is in danger or needs help, as well as steer clear of the Drowned.
<div class="onlydark">
===<span style= "font-family:Aleo; text-shadow: 1.5px 1.5px 0px #000000, 1px 1px 10px #45392d, 0px 0px 1px #000000; color:white;"><center>'''The Blood Trail'''</center></span>===
</div>
<div class="onlylight">
===<span style= "font-family:Aleo; text-shadow: 1.5px 1.5px 0px #1b1b1b, 1px 1px 10px #45392d, 0px 0px 1px #FFFFFF; color:black;"><center>'''The Blood Trail'''</center></span>===
</div>

'''The Blood Trail''' is a narrow, sandy trail that stretches infinitely across the level, and is distinctive for its crimson-red color compared to the level’s usual sea blue, which makes it easy to notice from a distance. A peculiar thing about the trail is that it does not touch any other underwater structure or entity in the level. Other than that, no other information is known due to a lack of sufficient documentation on the region.

It is unknown what the purpose of this trail is and whether it was manmade or not, but '''those who followed the trail have never returned'''.
</div>
<div class="header>Entity Presence</div>
'''Level 7.77''' is inhabited by one passive (possibly extinct) entity species that lives in the deeper areas of the level, which are the '''Drowned'''. All previous living things within '''Level 7.77''' are theorized to have been wiped out by this single entity.

<div class="onlydark">
===<span style= "font-family:Aleo; text-shadow: 1.5px 1.5px 0px #000000, 1px 1px 10px #45392d, 0px 0px 1px #000000; color:white;"><center>'''The Drowned'''</center></span>===
</div>
<div class="onlylight">
===<span style= "font-family:Aleo; text-shadow: 1.5px 1.5px 0px #1b1b1b, 1px 1px 10px #45392d, 0px 0px 1px #FFFFFF; color:black;"><center>'''The Drowned'''</center></span>===
</div>
[[File:Drown.jpg|center]]
<div style="text-align:center;">A photograph of a Drowned. Photographer unknown.
<br><br>
'''The Drowned''' are the only confirmed entities present in Level 7.77. They are described as corpse-like bodies with slight differences in appearance compared to the human body (e.g. a missing foot or an extra ear), donning clothing from all time periods. They are located in the deeper portions of the level, most commonly in the Cemetery and next to the Trail of Blood. Unlike most level-exclusive entities, they do not behave as active threats to wanderers and are usually reported as immobile, non-aggressive, and unresponsive. They are often found lying on the ground, positioned along the aforementioned areas, and seldom lying next to wreckage and debris in place. This overly passive nature of theirs has led many to theorise that these entities are, in fact, deceased (possibly killed by a superior entity yet to be discovered) and extinct. 

Even with the lack of active behavior, their presence is still a hindrance to wanderers. They cause navigational difficulties, as these bodies occupy space in hard-to-escape locations, such as narrow passages and tunnels. The bodies can also stack together to block direct routes, forcing wanderers into choosing tighter paths. In conclusion, '''the Drowned''' are unable to inflict any physical or mental damage, only posing a danger when it comes to navigation.

While this has not been confirmed, some wanderers have stated that '''the Drowned''' have caused them to “let their guard down”, with some wanderers stating that they have sometimes forgotten to go back to the surface for oxygen because of these entities, as well as decreasing their attention span and decision-making speed, resulting in difficulty in tight-passage navigation. </div>


<div class="header>Entrances and Exits</div>
===Entrances===
*Staying in a flooded area on any level for enough time leads one here.
===Exits===
*Wandering far enough beyond the level may lead one to a random level.
